% --- Section 3: IPO Valuation ---
\section{Indicative IPO Valuation}
The implied valuation ranges from \$1.46B to \$2.92B based on comparable infrastructure software peers. The peer group median trades at 9.0x EV/Revenue. For Canonical's base case, the multiple is stepped down 1.5 turns to 7.5x. This discount does not reflect weaker margins—Canonical's profitability is already higher than several loss-making peers—but rather adjusts for Canonical's smaller revenue scale (\$292M vs. the peer range of \$580M–\$1,680M) and a standard private-company illiquidity premium.

Applying a 7.5x multiple on FY24 revenue yields a base estimated EV of ~\$2.19B. A bull case hitting peer parity (10x) yields \$2.92B, while a conservative bear case (5x) anchors at \$1.46B.

